FT  12 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Schroders considers Wertheim takeover
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BARCHARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Schroders, the City merchant bank, confirmed yesterday that it is
considering taking full control of Wertheim, the Wall Street securities
house in which it has held a 50 per cent stake since 1986, writes David
Barchard.
However, the bank denied that active negotiations for a cash sale had got
under way. 'The future of our relationship with Wertheim has been under
discussion for some time, but there are no negotiations in progress,' the
bank said.
To acquire 100 per cent control of Wertheim, which made Dollars 30m profits
last year, would probably cost around Dollars 100m.
