<TEXT>
PORTSMOUTH-based WARINGS CONTRACTORS has beaten national competition to win
a Pounds 7m Ministry of Defence design and build contract for a new
headquarters building inside Portsmouth's naval base to house the combined
staffs of the Second Sea Lord and the Commander in Chief Naval Home Command.
