<HEADLINE>
FT  12 OCT 92 / Dish shortage curbs satellite installations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SHORTAGE of satellite dishes is slowing the growth of satellite television
in the important autumn season, Raymond Snoddy writes.
A survey of independent retailers by Continental Research, the independent
market research company, found that 78 per cent of outlets were experiencing
stock shortages, although supplies were now starting to improve.
Continental believes the shortage was a factor in a decline in installations
last month.
The FT Satellite Monitor shows that in September an estimated 61,000 new
dishes were installed, compared with 73,000 in August. There were 65,000
installations in September last year.
