<TEXT>
Iraqi Kurds attacked ridges guarding the last bastion of Turkish separatist
Kurds in northern Iraq yesterday, Reuter reports. Kurdish Peshmerga
guerrillas crept up rocky heights which command entry to the Hakurk valley,
where Turkey's Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) has its military command. The
assault, which could take several days, was the climax of a week-old
offensive to drive the PKK from their bases in northern Iraq.
