FT  10 OCT 92 / Finance &amp; The Family: Up and down the Misery Index
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The 'Misery Index', which adds the unemployment rate, expressed in
percentage terms, to the rate of inflation, fell last year because of the
drop in inflation from 9 per cent in January to 4.5 per cent in December
1991. It has been on the increase this year because of a steady rise in
unemployment, from 9.2 per cent in January to 9.9 per cent in August.
However, falls in inflation since May have helped to keep it down in recent
months.
